	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Oct 1st 11:16 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>    My two cents, form someone who wanted to spec conj but inadvertantly boosted spec evo quicker.  Until you start chaining pets regularly, spec evocation will be to your benefit.  Conjuration will then be more important if you either solo, or your pets tank a lot.  In good groups, mages are among the most mana efficient players, so specialization will not be as big a factor as you might think.  You'll be saving your mana for the overpulls or the corpse recoveries.  If you solo more, then in the long run it will help you more to specialize in conjuration, especially post-50.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
