<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100075429790227></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100075429790227><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100075429790227>RE: Which skill to specialize in?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100075429790227#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=92666><span id= >Papua</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>6 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Sep 17th 3:18 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You hit the nail on the head at the end of your post.  You should specialize conjuration for now, and switch to evocation later.<br><br>Specialization makes a massive difference in mana consumption.  Further, it goes up pretty fast.  So specialize in what you're using.  And when you switch to evocation, switch your specialization.<br><br>There's no point in specializing in evocation before you get your evocation spells.  So that leaves two alternatives:  specialize conjuration, or don't do anything with specialization until you get your evocation spells.  That's not an option, so you are left with only one option: specialize conjuration now, and switch later.<br><br>Be sure to put a point into everything, or else nothing will raise above 50.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
