<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99990224325344></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99990224325344><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99990224325344>Pet info for young'uns</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99990224325344#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Sep 7th 6:37 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, i'm going to try to shed some light on this pet discussion for all you folks. First, and MOST IMPORTANTLY, there is no best pet, as much as people love to say otherwise. It is ALL situational. I'll go through each one.<br><br>Earth<br>Hits quite hard, pet root (which does damage 51+). This is the pet i used for soloing from 29-51, and it still is. Has the most HPs, can't avoid hits worth a good goddamn. Still, the root spell, especially when used with Malise/Malisement/Malosi/Malosini, will save your arse if you overnuke - and there will be times when you need to in order to kill the mob. Be careful about using it in groups, when snare or fear kiting this pet can ruin the group's whole day with the root. Never forget, though, that it is a capable tank - i have been in groups where it was, in fact, the primary tank. Still - always was my highest priority pet.<br><br>Water<br>I don't have as much experience with this pet, but i used it extensively up till 29, when i got ambitious and started needing the HPs of earth. Still - great pet for fear kiting (especially post-49 when it turns into a rogue, although i personally have no experience with this yet) and general group usage. You won't piss anyone off with this pet like you will with earth. And never forget, it's immune to poison...<br><br>Air<br>Use against casters. Stuns are VERY nice, although usually a debuff will make it much more effective. Also did a nice group once with a rogue and a druid, air pet would stun, rogue would run around and backstab. Druid did druid things, like heal. I also made him DS cuz i was lazy. But i digress. Also a good pet for dungeons, the invis feature is handy... I've heard and seen mages use this pet as a tank, although i haven't tried this. Once i get 53 air, i think i will =)<br><br>Fire<br>Oh baby. Great pet, nothing ruins a greenie's day like a fire pet. The innate damage shield of a fire pet is better than anything you can put out, but its HPs are abysmally low. When fighting easy stuff, it's the weapon of choice, and it also has a good role in groups as a pure damage dealer.  Not to mention the fact that it's immune to fire, which makes it the only way to take down Lord Rak'Ashiir in the City of Mist (with his 2000 damage every 6 seconds AoE). SO yeah.<br><br>Mages - experiment. have fun with your pets. Get your focus items early. And keep current on spells =/<br><br>Enjoy the class =) feel free to /tell me with any mage-related questions.<br><br>Zalgyr Falconkeeper<br>51st Pet Molester of Bertoxxulous<br>Official Nihil Raid Bitch<br>Firm believer in the "/pet attack, /mage sleep" philosophy<br><br><br>"Zal, mod rods plz"<br>"zal, can i get a rod?"<br>"ok, i can take 3 rods now"<br>"coldstone plz zal"<br>"DS me"<br>"zal, can u summon me some food and water?"<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
