	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ill probably get flamed to death for posting with a lvl 51 Mage but this is just my opinion at lvl 20 the stats might change on the pets changing the rankings on higher lvls:<br><br>Earth:  Does not do high damage, has the most hitpoints and roots.  Most used pet when soloing following VERY CLOSE by Water.  The reason I think anyone would use the earth pet when soloing ,whether they realise it or not, (I use water when soloing) is the fact that they DO NOT DO A LOT OF DAMAGE and TAKE MORE DAMAGE.  It is well known that when you are soloing and your pet does 50% or more damage that it takes away from your XP.  I have used the earth pet but it just does not do that much damage but lives a long time and makes you throw more DD's causing you to to the most damage which is good for xp but drains mana more.<br><br>Water - My pet of choice for soloing.  The medium like the Human Race.  But its damage can steal from your xp so I always lead off the attack with a DD and if im lucky tcan get a second in before the Mob hits me aggroing my pet.  I always take the first hit to make sure I give more damage to the mob than my pet.<br><br>Air - Dont really know what to say about this pet.  Used it once in the oasis and he sucked.  His stun at this low 20 lvl dont proc that much and i wish you could turn him invisible by a pet command.  He seems to go invisible when he feels like and the ivisible seems to be like a PROC happening every so often.  Stun will be good against casters but at my level you only fight low number of casters at a time.<br><br>Fire - My group pet of choice.  The best damage and attack speed for most damage but the least amount of HP.  But in a group with tanks HP doesnt really matter for your pet because the aggro wont be on him all the ime, Ive found aggro only goes to him when your group is being overrun.  Tanks take the aggro and him doing more damage than you doesnt matter in a group situation as XP is not stolen.<br><br>Thats my 2p<br><br>Seriallova<br>20 Mage<br>Erollisi Marr<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
