	   <tr><td colspan=2>At level 51 your Vocerate:Earth pet can kill 3-4 Hill Giants in a row without ever resting or you casting a single DD. Just buff it and pull it some food. When it gets low use the ole' chain casting technique. It is 99% safe because your pet will keep the HGs rooted and give you plenty of time to step back a bit and get a new pet up. If you pull with malosi they will almost always be rooted. I am sure that you know the routine if you made it to level 51. Just sit back and watch Jabober go to work and rake all the cash in, you don't have to share with him. With all that gold you are sure to get run over to the gnome gem merchant and buy gems so that you don't get a weight problem.  The suggestion about OOT is a good one as well, most of the clopses will be blue so can get some exp and cash at the same time. If you go there be sure to keep your charisma gear handy for selling the gems. Good luck (Hey, you got me thinking...I could use 6k too)<br>PS You will probably anger the lower levels because you will decrease the HG population rapidly. I always try to keep my HG slaughtering to times when few people are on...<br><br>Ubunoa Yandini <br>Erudite Elementalist<br>Knights of Trinity-Quellious<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
