<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99957875253425></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99957875253425><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99957875253425>RE: lvl 18 now WHAT DO I DO......</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99957875253425#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Sep 4th 12:45 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am not sure if the problem lies in your tactics or in something else? Having soloed my way to lvl 60, here's my brief advice:<br>1. Always invest in pet buffs! Prior to attacking a mob, make sure fire shields are up (on you and on your pet) and the Burnout spell on!<br>2. Experiment with pets. Certain pets are massively better vs some mobs than others.<br>3. Fast nuking is often a bad idea. Keep the mob disinterested in you a good portion of the fight. If the mob is tough, stand back (further away), nuke hard, then kite the mob around while your pet takes free shots at its back!!!<br>4. Learn changing your view angles to watch the mob actions without having to face it! Using the first person (tunnel-vision) perspective = amateur play = die often.<br>5. Get a pair of jboots!!! The best solo hunter's aid in the game!<br>6. Group whenever you can...when I made my mage (in the early phases of EQ), grouping had not been buffed, so I got into the habit of soloing. But these days, the safety in numbers combines well with the experience rewards to the point where soloing is a b-class art.<br><br>If you want to SOLO, however, here are my suggestions for zones. At lvl 18 head to S Ro and lvl to 21. You might want to pick up a level or two at the crocks in Marr but after that you can go to S Karana and easily hit 30 plus killing treants or centaurs! After that make sure you have all four focus-item quests complete because at lvl 34 these items will strengthen your pets. From there on, lvls 34-45 happen in Overthere (if you're a good race this may NOT be as great of a place on acount of npc dark elf guards). Beyond that point you can either pick up a few levels in the Dreadlands or skip that and head straight for the Seafury Island in the Ocean of Tears (OOT).<br>At about lvl 53 go to Skyfire, although be warned, if soloing, mobs there will make you earn every inch of your existence, so be very careful!<br>It doesn't get easier after that, since a 50+ Magician is a very, very AWFUL class!!! But if you are an optimist, you can certainly finish up leveling by killing Sentient Suits in the Wakening Lands in Velious!<br><br>Later!<br>Yours, retired mage, formerly of the Tribunal server.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
