	   <tr><td colspan=2>I personnaly love my mage.  It is an awesome class.  I have been able to explore many many dungeons solo and have had a blast with the various item summoning spells.  I am looking forward to the new item spell from SoL.  About the only grip I have with the magician class would be the lack of varity in the damaging spells.  Basically it boils down to fire or magic based spells.  As "elementalists"  I think a better mix would have been fire and cold based spells.  Notice I dropped the magic based spell.  In my opinion this falls more in line with the Wizard class. (I'm giving a concession for the gain of cold based here)  As for the lack of root, well yes it would be nice but I have never found it to be an utter stop gap.  Work around this by using the earth pet.  I would say that I play solo 75% of the time and I am now almost 54th level.  My pets are amazing and I get many an awe from other players on their abilities.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
